This may also be the case when paying in an online shop or for other subscription services.</p>\n<p>It eliminates the need to type in your card details when you make purchases, saving you time. You can also use the debit card for recurring payments.</p>\n<p>When the debit card is digitalized, the sensitive card data is encrypted and turned into a type of secret code known as a token. To protect against misuse or data theft, only the token is saved instead of the sensitive card data. It can then be used to process future and/or recurring transactions.</p>\n<p>Find out more on our <a href=\"/content/six/global/en/site/debix-plus/digital-debit-card.html\">digital debit cards page</a>.</p>\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why is the logo of my bank (not) displayed in the application icon?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>As soon as a Debit Mastercard or Visa Debit is stored in the debiX+ app, the icon of the debiX+ app is automatically supplemented with the logo of the bank that issued the debit card.
